---
import DocPage from "../../../components/DocPage.astro";
const cb =
  "bg-background-dark p-3 border-l-2 border-border text-foreground-dark text-xs mb-6 overflow-x-auto";
---

<DocPage title="Configuration">
  <h1>Configuration</h1>

  <p>
    Shannon uses standard config locations — no custom config directory. Your
    existing nushell and bash config works automatically.
  </p>

  <h2>Config Locations</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Config</th><th>Location</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Bash</td>
        <td
          ><code class="text-secondary">~/.bash_profile</code> / <code
            class="text-secondary">~/.bashrc</code
          ></td
        >
        <td>PATH, env vars, nvm, homebrew, etc.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Nushell</td>
        <td><code class="text-secondary">~/.config/nushell/env.nu</code></td>
        <td>Nushell env setup</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Nushell</td>
        <td><code class="text-secondary">~/.config/nushell/config.nu</code></td>
        <td>Keybindings, colors, hooks, completions</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Nushell</td>
        <td><code class="text-secondary">~/.config/nushell/login.nu</code></td>
        <td>Login shell config</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Nushell</td>
        <td
          ><code class="text-secondary">~/.config/nushell/history.sqlite3</code
          ></td
        >
        <td>SQLite command history</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>None of these files are required. Shannon works out of the box.</p>

  <h2>Bash Config</h2>

  <p>
    Shannon's bash subprocess starts as a login shell (<code
      class="text-secondary">bash --login</code
    >), loading your <code class="text-secondary">~/.bash_profile</code> (which conventionally
    sources <code class="text-secondary">~/.bashrc</code>). At startup, the
    resulting env vars are captured and injected into nushell's Stack.
  </p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-muted"># ~/.bash_profile (or ~/.bashrc)</span>

<span class="text-muted"># Homebrew</span>
<span class="text-accent">eval</span> <span class="text-success">"$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"</span>

<span class="text-muted"># Custom paths</span>
<span class="text-accent">export</span> <span class="text-warning">PATH</span>=<span class="text-success">"$PATH:$HOME/.cargo/bin"</span>
<span class="text-accent">export</span> <span class="text-warning">PATH</span>=<span class="text-success">"$PATH:$HOME/.local/bin"</span>

<span class="text-muted"># Environment variables</span>
<span class="text-accent">export</span> <span class="text-warning">EDITOR</span>=<span class="text-success">"nvim"</span></code></pre>

  <p>
    Any tutorial that says "add this to your
    <code class="text-secondary">.bashrc</code>" — just do it. Shannon picks it
    up automatically.
  </p>

  <h2>Nushell Config</h2>

  <p>
    Nushell config lives in the standard <code class="text-secondary"
      >~/.config/nushell/</code
    >
    directory. If you already use nushell, Shannon shares your existing config. See
    the
    <a href="https://nushell.sh/book/configuration.html"
      >Nushell configuration docs</a
    >
    for full details.
  </p>

  <p>Common settings:</p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-muted"># ~/.config/nushell/config.nu</span>

<span class="text-warning">$env</span>.config.show_banner = <span class="text-danger">false</span>          <span class="text-muted"># disable startup banner</span>
<span class="text-warning">$env</span>.config.edit_mode = <span class="text-success">"vi"</span>             <span class="text-muted"># vi or emacs keybindings</span>
<span class="text-warning">$env</span>.config.history.file_format = <span class="text-success">"sqlite"</span></code></pre>

  <h2>Loading Order</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <code class="text-secondary">~/.bash_profile</code> → <code
        class="text-secondary">~/.bashrc</code
      > — bash login init (env vars injected into nushell)
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="text-secondary">~/.config/nushell/env.nu</code> — nushell environment
    </li>
    <li>
      <code class="text-secondary">~/.config/nushell/config.nu</code> — nushell settings
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Banner</h2>

  <p>
    The startup banner respects nushell's
    <code class="text-secondary">$env.config.show_banner</code> setting:
  </p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-warning">$env</span>.config.show_banner = <span class="text-danger">false</span>    <span class="text-muted"># no banner</span>
<span class="text-warning">$env</span>.config.show_banner = <span class="text-success">"short"</span>  <span class="text-muted"># just startup time</span>
<span class="text-warning">$env</span>.config.show_banner = <span class="text-danger">true</span>     <span class="text-muted"># full welcome message (default)</span></code></pre>
</DocPage>
